    <node id="1. According to Kirsty Williams AM, Major universities in the UK, including Cambridge and Oxford, value the Welsh Baccalaureate during the admissions process. Even if they do not use it as a formal part of their offer, they recognize its value in students' personal statements and interviews. The skills learned through the Welsh Baccalaureate are considered beneficial for the transition from A-level work to university-type work. There is no consensus that Welsh students are at a disadvantage when taking this qualification. Russell Group universities, including Oxford and Cambridge, have stated that there is no detriment to Welsh students who undertake the Welsh Baccalaureate, as they value the qualification and consider it useful for developing transition skills." />
