nal guidance and support for FE colleges regarding the suitability and benefits of the Welsh Baccalaureate for high-achieving students. Sharing research on academic outcomes and skill development associated with the Baccalaureate, as well as best practices from successful colleges, could help integrate it into curricula for top-performing students.&#10;&#10;In summary, FE colleges may be exempting their highest performing students from the Welsh Baccalaureate due to concerns about academic rigor and relevance, a potential distraction from core subjects, or a lack of information on the benefits of the qualification. Addressing these concerns requires collaboration between education authorities, teachers, parents, and students, as well as ongoing communication, professional development opportunities, and resources to support the implementation and integration of the Baccalaureate into FE college curricula.">
