by taking this qualification, as universities across the UK recognize its value, including Russell Group universities. A Qualifications Wales representative also works to ensure that UK universities understand the value of Welsh qualifications.&#10;4. While there have been some concerns raised about balancing the Welsh Bac with other qualifications and well-being issues, overall, it is valued by many universities as an equivalent to an A-level or a factor in lowering offer requirements for certain courses. Employers were involved in developing the qualification, and many appreciate the skills students acquire through it.">
