ce and internships, as they are highly valued by employers. This means that students who have completed project-based, individual-led, research-based work such as the Welsh baccalaureate or EPQ may have an advantage when it comes to securing work experience and internships during their undergraduate studies.&#10;4. Overall, there is a positive correlation between students who have engaged in project-based, individual-led, research-based work such as the Welsh baccalaureate and EPQ qualifications in the UK, and their potential success in undergraduate studies and gaining work experience.">
