nized as a valuable and rigorous qualification, thus enhancing its value and addressing concerns about its perceived lack of rigor.&#10;3. By having a grading system and independent benchmarking process in place, the Welsh Baccalaureate can be more consistently valued and understood by universities and employers across the UK. This ensures that Welsh students are not disadvantaged when applying for further education or jobs, as their qualifications will be recognized and appreciated for their rigor and value.&#10;4. The combination of a grading system and independent benchmarking process can help to dispel negative perceptions about the Welsh Baccalaureate, such as claims that it lacks rigor, is passively marked, or has grades that are inflated. By demonstrating the credibility and value of the qualification, these concerns can be addressed, and the Welsh Baccalaureate can be seen as a genuinely rigorous and valuable educational experience for students in Wales.">
