    <edge source=", important topics such as citizenship, enterprise, financial capability and sustainability.' So, the prime driver for our ITE reforms, obviously, is the preparedness for 'Successful Futures', but in preparing our teachers to be in a position to successfully deliver that, those are also the pedagogical principles and that shift in pedagogy that we see aligned to the Welsh baccalaureate. So, it is actually a part of the accreditation process that the curriculum that the new ITE providers will have to deliver—ensuring that teachers have those skills and have that confidence to be able to deliver their teaching in a way that, as I said, ensures that we successfully deliver on Donaldson, but also on the same pedagogical principles that are needed for the successful delivery of the Welsh bac.&#10;Speaker: Suzy Davies AM&#10;Content: In the pre-Donaldson period, then, bearing in mind what you've just said, do you expect to see a surge in improvement on how the baccalaureate is taken up by those schools that are currently less keen on it?&#10;Speaker: Kirsty Williams AM&#10;Content: I hope that we will see increased numbers of students taking the qualification and an increase in the quality" target="1. ITE reforms: The accreditation process for ITE programs now includes a criterion that requires teachers to help students make connections across their learning, focusing on important topics such as citizenship, enterprise, financial capability, and sustainability. This change is intended to prepare teachers to effectively deliver the Welsh Baccalaureate and other connected learning experiences.&#10;&#10;2. Professional learning: The Welsh Government emphasizes the importance of professional learning for in-service teachers to ensure they have the necessary skills and confidence to teach the Welsh Baccalaureate effectively. This is addressed through funding allocated to consortia, which then distribute it to individual schools based on their specific professional learning needs, including the ability to deliver the Welsh Baccalaureate.&#10;&#10;3. Curriculum alignment: The new curriculum in ITE programs focuses on elements of 'Successful Futures', which are closely aligned with the skills and knowledge required for the Welsh Baccalaureate Challenge Certificate. This overlap provides opportunities to reinforce the value of the Welsh Baccalaureate within initial teacher education, emphasizing its importance to students, teachers, and school leaders.&#10;&#10;4. Strengthening guidance: In response to concerns from teachers who feel undermined by parents' calls to the Welsh Government, there is a plan to strengthen and clarify guidance for school leaders regarding decision-making on suitable qualifications for students. This step aims to ensure consistency in approach, prevent confusion, and maintain positive relationships between teachers, parents, and educational authorities.">
