ities for regional consortia support and WJEC resources will be available, as well as a national approach to professional learning focused on addressing the professional learning needs of those already in the system.&#10;4. The government is also reforming Initial Teacher Education (ITE) to prepare teachers for 'Successful Futures' and delivering the Welsh baccalaureate with the required pedagogical principles. Ensuring teachers have these skills is part of the accreditation process for new ITE providers.&#10;5. By addressing these concerns and creating an enabling environment through professional learning opportunities, the Welsh government aims to foster consistency in delivering the qualification and maintain positive relationships between teachers, parents, and educational authorities.">
