nt associated with the Baccalaureate, as well as best practices from colleges that have successfully integrated it into their curriculum for top-performing students.&#10;5. Ultimately, addressing the concerns of FE colleges about the Welsh Baccalaureate will require a collaborative effort between education authorities, teachers, parents, and students to ensure that all parties understand the value and significance of the qualification for future success. This may involve ongoing communication, professional development opportunities, and resources to support the implementation and integration of the Baccalaureate into FE college curricula.">
